    "cooking_instructions": [
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Boil a kettle</p><p>Top, tail, peel and finely chop your <strong>carrot[s]</strong></p><p>Peel and finely chop your<strong> brown onion[s]</strong></p>",
            "order": 1,
            "image": "/images/instructions/meat-free-wholewheat-spaghetti-bolognese/step-1.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Heat a large, wide-based pan (preferably non-stick) with a drizzle of <strong>olive oil</strong> over a medium-high heat</p><p>Once hot, add the <strong>chopped onion</strong> and<strong> carrot</strong> and cook for 5-6 min or until beginning to soften</p>",
            "order": 2,
            "image": "/images/instructions/meat-free-wholewheat-spaghetti-bolognese/step-2.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Meanwhile, peel and finely chop (or grate) your <strong>garlic</strong></p>",
            "order": 3,
            "image": "/images/instructions/meat-free-wholewheat-spaghetti-bolognese/step-3.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Once the onion and carrot are beginning to soften, add your<strong> meat-free mince</strong> (remove the paper if required!) to the pan and reduce the heat to medium</p><p>Cook for 7-8 min or until browned all over, breaking it up with a wooden spoon as you go</p>",
            "order": 4,
            "image": "/images/instructions/meat-free-wholewheat-spaghetti-bolognese/step-4.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>While the mince is cooking, add your <strong>pasta </strong>to a pot of <strong>boiled water</strong> and bring to the boil over a high heat</p><p>Cook the pasta<strong> </strong>for 7-9 min (10-12 min for wholewheat) or until cooked with a slight bite, then drain, reserving a cup of the <strong>starchy pasta water</strong></p><p>Meanwhile, dissolve your<strong> vegetable stock mix </strong>and <strong>soy sauce</strong> in 200ml <span class=\"text-purple\">[300ml] </span><span class=\"text-danger\">[400ml]</span> <strong>boiled water </strong>\u2013 this is your<strong> stock</strong></p>",
            "order": 5,
            "image": "/images/instructions/meat-free-wholewheat-spaghetti-bolognese/step-5.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Add the<strong> chopped garlic </strong>to the pan with your <strong>tomato paste</strong> and <strong>dried oregano</strong> and cook for 30 secs or until fragrant</p><p>Once fragrant, add the<strong> stock </strong>with your <strong>chopped</strong> <strong>tomatoes</strong> and a generous pinch of <strong>sugar</strong>, <strong>salt</strong> and <strong>black pepper</strong></p><p>Bring to the boil and cook for 5 min further or until thickened and the mince is cooked through \u2013 this is your <strong>meat-free mince bolognese</strong></p>",
            "order": 6,
            "image": "/images/instructions/meat-free-wholewheat-spaghetti-bolognese/step-6.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Grate your <strong>Italian hard cheese</strong> finely</p><p>Add the<strong> cooked pasta </strong>to the <strong>meat-free mince bolognese </strong>with a splash of<strong> starchy pasta water </strong>and a small pinch of <strong>salt</strong> and give everything a good mix up \u2013 this is your <strong>meat-free mince spaghetti bolognese</strong></p>",
            "order": 7,
            "image": "/images/instructions/meat-free-wholewheat-spaghetti-bolognese/step-7.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Serve the <strong>meat-free mince spaghetti bolognese</strong></p><p>Top with the <strong>grated Italian hard cheese</strong></p><p>Enjoy!</p><p><strong><span class=\"text-danger\">Loved this recipe? Keep an eye out for it on the Everyday Favourites section of our menu.</span></strong></p>",
            "order": 8
        }
    ],
